\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. A. calycocarpum} Rupr.,{\i  Mém. Acad. Sci. Pétersb.}{\b  15}({\b 2}): 103 (1869). Erect perennial 15-35 cm; indumentum dimorphic on the inflorescence, grey-white; non-flowering stems more or less long. Lower leaves obovate or obovate-orbicular, obtuse, the upper oblanceolate. Raceme elongate in fruit; pedicels up to 9 mm, patent or erecto-patent. Sepals 2·5-4 mm; petals 4-7 mm. Silicula 4·5-6·5 mm, orbicular or orbicular-ovate, densely pubescent; valves inflated, with flattened margin; style 2-3·5 mm. Seeds c. 3 mm, winged.{\i  Dry, rocky slopes. • Krym.} Rs(K).
