\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 31. A. pulvinare} Velen.,{\i  Sitz.-Ber. Böhm. Ges. Wiss. }{\b 1889}: 30 (1889). Caespitose perennial 6-15 cm, with numerous rosettes and short non-flowering stems; indumentum dimorphic, grey. Basal leaves oblanceolate or spathulate, the upper lanceolate-spathulate, long-petiolate; hairs c. 1 mm in diameter. Racemes elongate in fruit; pedicels up to 8 mm. Sepals 3-4 mm; petals 5-6 mm, obovate, abruptly attenuate into claw. Silicula 4-5·5 mm, elliptical to suborbicular, pubescent; valves inflated, with a flattened margin; style 3-5 mm. Seeds c. 1·5 mm, broadly winged. 2n = 32. •{\i  C. part of Balkan peninsula southwards to C. Greece; Romania.} Bu Gr Ju Rm.
