\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 32. A. montanum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 650 (1753) (incl. {\i A. thessalum} Halácsy, {\i A. vourinonense} T.R. Dudley & Rech. fil.). Procumbent to erect, green to almost white perennial 5-25 cm, with non-flowering rosettes or short stems. Basal leaves oblong or oblanceolate-spathulate, the upper linear or linear-spathulate; hairs 0·4-0·7 mm in diameter, 6- to 24-rayed. Raceme elongate in fruit; pedicels 4-6 mm, patent or erecto-patent. Sepals 2·5-3·5 mm; petals emarginate. Silicula 3-5·5 mm; valves inflated, with flattened margin. Seeds 1·5-2 mm; wing 0·2-0·4 mm wide.{\i  Most of Europe except the north, much of the west and the islands}. Al Au Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(B, C, W, K, E) Tu.
